{
  "stem": "24814.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No sanitation, no water or anything, and he was one of, what, half a dozen people that lived when they opened the doors and the dead bodies fell out.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And that was-- one man told-- many of them had been in the transport trains, and they all had pretty much the same story.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They were the 10% that survived that little process.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And then they would talk about certain guards.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN], they'd say.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[SPEAKING GERMAN], frightful, frightful, who would be just sadists, who were allowed to take out their sadism on prisoners.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some-- they made a big distinction between a-- a guard that was not too bad and a guard that was horrible, the guards that just carried out orders and the ones that went way beyond, they just killed people.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I heard many, many, they'd say-- those who had been in a camp together someplace.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You know, they moved them around the different camps for various reasons.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I never understood why.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They'd say, oh, so at Auschwitz or something, oh, [SPEAKING GERMAN].",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A particular guard.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Many of the guards that were the worst, according to the prisoners, were Ukrainians, by the way, which is a fact not sufficiently appreciated today.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The-- you'd mention Ukrainer, and they all start swearing and cursing.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They had all had terrible treatment from Ukrainian guards, who worked for the Germans.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Apparently, anti-Semitism is a way of life in the Ukraine for a lot of people.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "[DRINKS] And they were unanimous in saying-- if possible-- is it a possibly worse than a German-- they'd say, yeah, Ukrainer is worse.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
